The paper deals with the design and analysis of auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.AI). The use of benchmark functions and competitive analysis is also relevant to optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.DS). The paper specifically focuses on online auctions and unlimited supply auctions, which are subtopics in electronic commerce (cs.EC). Finally, the use of a decomposition lemma and divide-and-conquer approach is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
